Patch summary:
Allow the software media codec process to read Cuttlefish graphics debug
properties labelled by the Cuttlefish graphics policy. minigbm probes
`vendor.minigbm.debug` through the shared graphics stack; once Cuttlefish gives
that property a specific vendor type, mediaswcodec needs the matching read rule
instead of falling back to the old default-property dontaudit.

diff --git a/cros_gralloc/sepolicy/mediaswcodec.te b/cros_gralloc/sepolicy/mediaswcodec.te
index a39fd73..9c17ec4 100644
--- a/cros_gralloc/sepolicy/mediaswcodec.te
+++ b/cros_gralloc/sepolicy/mediaswcodec.te
@@ -1,3 +1,5 @@
 # Suppress warnings for minigbm trying to read vendor.minigbm.debug
 # property for the devices which do not use this property.
 dontaudit mediaswcodec vendor_default_prop:file read;
+
+get_prop(mediaswcodec, vendor_graphics_debug_prop)
